known for her homespun columns on everything from gardening to
politics, died at her home in Florida Sunday morning. She was 85.
Ms. Sibley was the author of 25 books, four of them murder
mysteries, but she was best known for the columns she wrote for the
Atlanta Journal-Constitution for more than 50 years. (Emerson,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 25. WITH PHOTOS.
