<P>
   DALAILAMA _ DAYTON _ Transcendence from selfish concerns: By its
very nature, Buddhism seems incompatible with an American consumer
society fueled by manufactured needs. Five hundred years older than
Christianity, conceived in India and exported throughout most of
Asia, Buddhism increasingly appeals to the intellectual curiosity
and spiritual hunger of contemporary Westerners, too. It is ironic,
then, that the Dalai Lama comes to Indiana this week, not so much
as an ambassador for Buddhism, but to deliver a message that is
most startling to hear from a religious leader: That is, religion
doesn't matter. (Dayton Daily News). 31. WITH PHOTOS. MOVED.
