<TEXT>
<P>
   ATTENTION POLITICAL EDITORS
</P>
<P>
   A column about the straw poll in Iowa by Tom Baxter, who covers
politics for The Atlanta Journal-Constitution, has moved on the
wire with a category of (p) Politics. It is for immediate release.
If you have any questions about this column, call the Cox News
Service in Atlanta at 404 526-5456. Here is a budget line for the
column:
</P>
<P>
   BAXTER-COLUMN16-COX _ AMES, Iowa _ Any discussion of the winners
and losers in Saturday's much ballyhooed Iowa straw poll should
begin with a backward glance at some of those who polled well in
the past. Sen. Phil Gramm tied Bob Dole in the 1995 contest and
went swiftly nowhere. In 1987, Pat Robertson soundly beat George
Bush the elder, inspiring hopes that were never realized. With that
in mind, Texas Gov. George W. Bush might not take much consolation
in his first-place finish Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
