<HEADLINE>
OFF THE WALL
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   First she's killed off on ``Sunset Beach'' and now from ``Sports
Central.''
</P>
<P>
   A week after Sports Illustrated did an ain't-she-sweet feature
on her double life as a soap vixen and a sportscaster, Lisa
Guerrero was released from her contract at KCBS-Channel 2.
</P>
<P>
   KCBS offered her a seven-year contract that would have paid her
about 20 percent less than she had been making. So she's off to New
York to check out her acting options.
</P>
<P>
   KCAL-Channel 9 recently tried to hire her. KTTV-Channel 11 and
the Fox family are interested. And you gotta think KTLA-Channel 5
might have an opening soon. . . .
</P>
<P>
   __ Numbers-crunching Angels management should look into picking
up mind-numbing Raul Mondesi. Since neither one seems to be
committed to Southern California baseball any more. . . .
</P>
<P>
   __ Scottie Pippen, no matter what stunt his agent is trying to
broker with Houston, and Dennis Rodman, no matter how hard Phil
Jackson begs Jerry West, will be Lakers as soon as Warren Beatty
moves to the West Wing. . . .
</P>
<P>
   __ After a scheduled appearance on ABC's ``Politically
Incorrect'' this Wednesday night, Master Shaq Daddy is supposta
show Friday at The Source Hip-Hop Music Awards. Which might help
answer the question: How's the free throwin' going this summer? . .
.
</P>
<P>
   __ Modern Maturity magazine decided former Lakers and current
Miami Heat coach Pat Riley belongs among its ``sexiest stars over
50.'' New York Knicks coach Jeff Van Gundy was on the original list
until someone discovered he was neither over 50 nor sexy. . . .
</P>
<P>
   __ And Monica Seles is only 25? . . .
</P>
<P>
   __ Separated somewhere in the gene pool: Tiger Woods and Ruthie
from MTV's ``Real World.'' . . .
</P>
<P>
   __ Who doesn't do a Skip Caray imitation these days?. . . .
</P>
<P>
   __ Updated stats for Chin-Feng Chen, the Dodgers' Single-A San
Bernardino up-and-comer who, although far-fetched, would be an
interesting September callup: 110 games, .311 average, 24 homers,
101 RBI, 82 runs, .563 slugging percentage, 29 steals. . . .
</P>
<P>
   __ Maybe we're not dialed in, but no one's given us a clear
signal yet as to how these high school Area Code all-star games
will be affected by the new layover numbers. . . .
</P>
<P>
   __ Richie Phillips or Jimmy Hoffa _ which will be found someday
wrapped up in an umpire's chest protector beneath home plate at
Milwaukee County Stadium?. . . .
</P>
<P>
   __ The NASL is alive. It just goes by the name Northridge Arena
Soccer League, having fun out behind the Northridge Fashion Center.
. . .
</P>
<P>
   __ For what it's worth, Major League Soccer, on a per-game
basis, is drawing fewer fans than the NFL Europe League did this
past summer.
</P>
<P>
   An average of 17,845 watched North American-style football in
Europe; an average of 15,174 are watching European-style football
in American, according to Amateur Athletic Foundation of Los
Angeles researchers who cared enough to look into this. . . .
</P>
<P>
   __ And the Rose Bowl might have been packed with 90,185 to see
the Women's World Cup soccer final last month, but despite media
claims of that being a record-setting event for women's sports, the
AAF has found proof of bigger crowds.
</P>
<P>
   At least twice, more than 100,000 attended a women's soccer
game, the recent AAF newsletter reported.
</P>
<P>
   In 1971, a six-nation women's soccer tournament in Mexico drew
an estimated 108,000 for the opening match between Mexico and
Argentina. Later, the final between Denmark and Mexico also drew
100,000-plus. But this goes with an asterisk. According to
researchers from Leichester University, the tournament opener was
run on ``crassly sexist, showbiz/commercial lines'' and was
preceded by rodeos, baseball games and displays by ``semi-clad
majorettes'' that attracted a large throng of male spectators.
</P>
<P>
   Meaning, Brandi Chastain's strip show wasn't even original.
</P>
</TEXT>
