<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BC-KAN-BUDGET-KAN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
   
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Kansas City Star plans to move the following stories for use
by clients of the NYTimes News Service for AMs and PMs of Monday,
Aug. 16, 1999. If you have any questions, please call Miranda
Kennedy on the Star's News Desk at (816) 234-4720.
</P>
<P>
   STRAWPOLL-DOLE (DES MOINES, Iowa) _ The pundits' old
conventional wisdom on Elizabeth Dole's campaign: a disappointment.
The new: definitely back in the game. With a third-place finish in
Saturday's Iowa straw poll, Dole re-established herself as a
top-tier Republican presidential contender who is prepared to go
the distance against front-runner George W. Bush, the Texas
governor. By STEVE KRASKE. Story will move in the ``a'' and ``w''
categories.
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-VFW (KANSAS CITY, Mo.) _ President Clinton comes to
Kansas City today to mark the 100th anniversary of the Veterans of
Foreign Wars. His first appearance before a full convention of the
VFW _ he spoke to a smaller legislative conference of the group in
1995 _ has been greeted with scattered protests by some veterans.
By SCOTT CANON. Story will move in the ``a'' and ``w'' categories.
</P>
<P>
   HEASTER-COLUMN _ Economics column by JERRY HEASTER. Story will
move in the ``f'' category.
</P>
</TEXT>
