   (NYT19) EDGEMONT, N.Y. -- Aug. 15, 1999 --
CLINTON-HOUSEHUNTING-2, 8-15 -- A $1.7 million hilltop house on a
corkscrew of a major street known to locals as ``Suicide Hill,'' is
one of the houses President Clinton and his wife, Hillary, are
looking at in the New York region. As Clinton prepares to leave
public life and Mrs. Clinton gears up for an effort to join it, the
family swept through the wealthy New York City suburbs on Sunday
with about as much casualness as one can muster when accompanied by
a black sedan, two sport-utility vehicles, three police cruisers
and four mini-vans. (Richard L. Harbus/New York Times Photo)
